        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/ring_fault> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Fluid Flow Process"@en ;
    skos:topConceptOf cs: ;
.

<https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/Solid_Earth_Setting>
    a skos:Concept ;
    skos:definition "A SETTING in which bedrock UNITS are related to the configuration of the bedrock geology itself; these UNITS represent a broad range of scales and lithologies and can be the product of tectonic deformation and volcanic activity. The SOLID EARTH SETTING excludes UNITS formed by other processes (e.g. FLUVIAL - SUBAERIAL CHANNELS incised into bedrock) and is not intended to span the spectrum of geological terminology that is traditionally applied during terrestrial geology mapping."@en ;
    skos:inScheme cs: ;
    skos:narrower
        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/abyssal_hill> ,
        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/axial_volcanic_ridge> ,
        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/bedding_ridge> ,
        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/bedrock_outcrop_undef> ,
        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/dip_slope> ,
        <https://pid.geoscience.gov.au/def/voc/ga/GeomorphologySettings/impact_crater> ,
